item.title: ‚ö†Ô∏è‚ÄºÔ∏è VERYYY IMPORTANT | UNKOWN SECRETS OF MEDICAL INDUSTRY | Ft Sudhakar Kancharla Telugu Podcast |
item.description:
Before marriages in India families sit together, horoscope charts and kundalis are compared, and futures are predicted and decided.
But rarely do we ask a far more tangible question: What do our health reports say?
What does the cell reveal about our fate? If your father has hair fall or diabetes, is it coincidence or inheritance? What does it mean when one says it ‚Äúruns in the family‚Äù?
The answer lies in DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid), the biological blueprint that quietly shapes who we are. It influences whether we are tall or short, our eye color, our metabolism, our athletic potential, and even our susceptibility to conditions such as diabetes, cancer, and certain neurodevelopmental disorders like autism.
In this episode, we move the conversation from astrology to biology.
We sit down with Sudhakar Kancharla, founder of Yoda Diagnostics, one of India‚Äôs largest DNA diagnostics laboratories, to understand what our genes really reveal, and what they do not.
From the realities of at-home blood sample collection to the science behind genetic compatibility and inter-caste marriages, from Yoda‚Äôs DNA Decoder tests to the role of AI in predicting and preventing disease this conversation explores how data, diagnostics, and technology are reshaping healthcare in India. . The U.S. government has released around 3 million pages of related documents, while reports suggest millions more remain unreleased, sparking public demand for full transparency. item.title: ‚ù§Ô∏è‚Äçüî•India ka Dhurandhar's #telugupodcast #rrrshow #rohithgollena #indianarmy
item.description:
In this impactful telugu podcast episode on lazymuscle RRRshow, host Rohit Gollena brings an exclusive conversation with NSG Major General Ravi Ravada (Retd.), offering rare insights into India‚Äôs elite counter-terrorism force and the realities of modern warfare. This episode begins with a clear explanation of what is NSG, its role in national security, and why it is considered India‚Äôs ultimate tactical response unit for terror threats and hostage rescue missions. The discussion takes a deep dive into how NSG handled the Mumbai 26/11 attacks, covering operational planning, on-ground challenges, and lessons learned from one of the most complex counter-terror operations in Indian history. Major General Ravi Ravada explains the structure and purpose of the Black Tornado unit and the highly specialized 51 SAG, shedding light on how these commandos are trained to operate in high-risk urban environments. A powerful emotional segment focuses on Major Sandeep Unnikrishnan, the sofa associated with his final stand during 26/11, and the meaning of supreme sacrifice. This part of the telugu podcast reflects the emotional strength required by soldiers and the unseen cost paid by their families and comrades. The episode also explores the hardest NSG training routines and compares them with the even more demanding training of Indian PARA SF. From physical endurance to mental resilience, this conversation reveals why only the toughest soldiers qualify for elite forces. Major General Ravi Ravada shares experiences from missions he was involved in, leadership lessons from the battlefield, and decision-making under extreme pressure. Strategic national security topics such as the Uri surgical strike, ongoing issues at the India-China border, and evolving military threats are discussed in detail. Viewers will also learn about different types of weapons used in the Indian Army, the technological superiority and greatness of the BrahMos missile, and its importance in India‚Äôs defense doctrine. This rohith gollena hosted lazymuscle episode concludes with a discussion on the toughest emotional moment faced by a soldier, making this episode a must-watch telugu podcast for defense aspirants, patriotic youth, and anyone interested in India‚Äôs military power and real-life heroism.

item.title: FASTEST Way To Learn Python in 2026!
item.description:
Vishakha Sadhwani: FASTEST Way To Learn Python in 2026!
Cloud Python isn‚Äôt about algorithms or leetcode. It‚Äôs about automating infrastructure, integrating services, and handling failures at scale.
Variables manage configs and resource names. Loops help you operate across servers and buckets. Functions make automation reusable. Error handling saves you from flaky APIs. List comprehensions filter cloud resources fast. Libraries connect you to AWS, GCP, Azure, or OCI. API calls trigger workflows and fetch metrics. JSON parsing is how every cloud service communicates.
These concepts power most real-world cloud scripts.

item.title: Azure Data Engineering Demo for Beginners | Walkthrough
item.description:
In this Azure Data Engineering demo, we walk through an end-to-end mini project using real-world scenarios. You will learn how modern data pipelines are built on Microsoft Azure using core services like Azure Data Factory, Azure Databricks, Azure Synapse, and Azure Storage.
What you will learn: - Azure Data Engineering basics (ETL vs ELT, batch vs streaming) - Designing a simple data pipeline end-to-end - Ingesting data into Azure Data Lake Storage - Transformations using Azure Databricks / Spark - Loading data into a reporting/analytics layer - Best practices, tips and common interview points
Who is this for: - Freshers looking for Azure Data Engineer roles - Manual testers / support engineers planning to switch to data engineering - Working professionals moving from SQL / BI / On‚ÄëPrem to Azure - Anyone preparing for Azure Data Engineer interviews

item.title: If I Started My Tech Career In 2026, I Would Do THIS | Vishakha Sadhwani
item.description:
Learning Resources: https://github.com/vishakhasadhwani/cloud-skills-roadmap
If I started my tech career in 2026, this is exactly how I‚Äôd do it.
The biggest problem today isn‚Äôt lack of guidance, it‚Äôs too much advice. Roadmaps, frameworks, certifications, checklists. Most of them look great on paper but completely fall apart when you see how real production systems work. Real environments are messy. Decisions are driven by cost, legacy systems, compliance, and trade-offs‚Äînot by chasing the latest cloud service.

item.title: COMPLETE Cloud Security Roadmap for Beginners[2026]
item.description:
Vishakha Sadhwani: COMPLETE Cloud Security Roadmap for Beginners [2026]
In this short, I‚Äôll walk you through the 4 most crucial skills you need to become a Cloud Security Engineer.
Most Cloud Security Engineers step into this role with a Bachelor‚Äôs or Master‚Äôs degree in fields such as: ‚Ä¢ Cybersecurity ‚Ä¢ Information Security ‚Ä¢ Computer Science (though not always mandatory)
Top 4 Skills That Get You Hired Cloud Platform Basics ‚Äì Understand how AWS, Azure, and GCP work. Focus on their main services like Compute, Networking, and Storage.
Identity and Access Management (IAM) ‚Äì Learn how to create, manage, and restrict user permissions. Get comfortable with the principle of least privilege, Role-Based Access Control, and MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication).
Cloud Security Tools ‚Äì Practice with tools like AWS GuardDuty, Azure Security Center, and GCP Security Command Center.
Networking and Security Concepts ‚Äì Know the basics of firewalls, encryption, VPNs, and network segmentation.
With these skills, you can apply for roles like: ‚Ä¢Cloud Support Engineer (Security) ‚Ä¢Security Operations Engineer ‚Ä¢Cloud Security Architect

item.title: The Real Housewives of Salt Lake City
item.description:
A new show has been added to showRSS: The Real Housewives of Salt Lake City.

The Real Housewives of Salt Lake City takes viewers into an undiscovered world that is about so much more than religion, although the Mormon church is undeniably engrained in the culture. In the majestic mountains of Utah is a hidden social circle made up of successful women who have created their own paradise filled with luxury homes, shopping sprees and multi-million-dollar businesses and brands. With Hollywood's exclusive Sundance Film Festival in their backyards, these Type-A power-brokers are accustomed to rubbing elbows with A-listers and what party list you are on means everything. They have mastered running wildly successful enterprises by day and enjoy apr√®s ski at the finest resorts by night, all the while raising extraordinary and unconventional families. Here perfection is not an aspiration, it's a mandate. They hold themselves and each other to an extremely high standard and never hold back when things go sideways, but lord knows they are always there for each other when they need it most.
